======================================================================
INNER-CELL THINK LAYER · proof of concept
======================================================================

PROBLEM: produce the first 8 fibonacci numbers via shape-AST program.
         expected output: [0, 1, 1, 2, 3, 5, 8, 13]

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
STAGE 1 · try with v0.2 alphabet (no arithmetic)
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  [ipfs] base alphabet pinned as shp-4c6ab48969be3777
  [think] alphabet: shp-4c6ab48969be3777 (10 verbs)
  [think] generating candidates with v0.2 verbs only...
  [think] candidate 'direct-render' would smuggle expected values as literals — rejecting (not generalisable).
  [think] candidate 'loop-without-arith' → score 0.06 ops=43 ok=True err=None
  [think] EXHAUSTED. best score 0.06 (need 1.00). diagnosis:
          fibonacci requires updating an accumulator: a, b := b, a+b
          v0.2 alphabet has no primitive for arithmetic addition.
          DNA mutation cannot help — no rearrangement of existing verbs computes a sum.
  [stage 1] FAILED — as predicted. The alphabet structurally cannot express addition.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
STAGE 2 · DNA mutation (rearrange existing primitives)
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  [dna] no rearrangement of existing verbs can synthesise addition.
  [dna] every permutation of {↻, ↓, ↑, ◇, cmp, △, ◯} produces no sum.
  [dna] proven by closed-grammar analysis: type signatures don't compose to + .
  [stage 2] FAILED — as predicted. Need language evolution, not DNA tweaking.

